# Basic Definitions for Stopping Time Theory

This module provides fundamental definitions and basic properties
for stopping times in discrete probability spaces.

## Main Definitions

- `StoppingTime`: A random variable representing the first hitting time
- `UniformSum`: The cumulative sum of independent uniform [0,1) random variables

## References

- Billingsley, Patrick. "Probability and Measure"
- Ross, Sheldon M. "Stochastic Processes"
- Williams, David. "Probability with Martingales"
-/

